        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(qa): crabline channel driver",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR makes QA profile channel drivers executable and separates channel selection from the driver that provides it.\n\n- Adds `crabline` as a QA Lab devDependency pinned to merged Crabline main commit `f7d034d90a8005c61fe38216462f385b9fe9f018`.\n- Runs the `smoke-ci` Crabline path by asking Crabline for an OpenClaw adapter, then using the returned binding to configure OpenClaw's normal channel plugin against a Crabline fake provider server.\n- Keeps the default synthetic QA path as `qa-channel`, keeps `live` declarative for release-profile wiring, and normalizes `qa-channel | crabline | live` before driver-specific setup.\n- Keeps channel support, fake-provider startup, OpenClaw plugin config, target mapping, inbound payload mapping, and recorder decoding in Crabline's OpenClaw adapter instead of duplicating those semantics in QA Lab.\n- Keeps Crabline scoped to QA Lab as a devDependency, with an explicit QA Lab-only contract exception for the optional runtime import so it does not become a production runtime dependency.\n\n## Why\n\nQA scenarios should ask for a channel such as `telegram`, while the selected profile decides whether that exchange uses the synthetic QA channel, a Crabline fake provider server, or a live provider. `smoke-ci` is the deterministic Crabline profile; release evidence remains reserved for live channel drivers.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`\n- `pnpm --filter @openclaw/qa-lab exec tsgo --noEmit -p tsconfig.json`\n- `pnpm exec vitest run extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-channel-driver.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/suite-runtime-agent-process.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/extension-runtime-dependencies.contract.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_ADDITIONAL_BOUNDARY_SHARD='2/4,3/4,4/4' OPENCLAW_ADDITIONAL_BOUNDARY_CONCURRENCY=4 node scripts/run-additional-boundary-checks.mjs`\n- `pnpm openclaw qa suite --scenario dm-chat-baseline --channel-driver crabline --channel telegram --provider-mode mock-openai --output-dir .artifacts/qa-e2e/crabline-dm-smoke --fast`\n- `git diff --check`\n",
